mmary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JVM args for testing**\\n\\nI’m thinking about JVM args and how to set up test-code. The idea is to include environment variables, system properties, and other test-code setups in `agent_guidance`. I might need the `--add-opens java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` argument for testing. However, I have to be cautious about when to apply it. It's interesting that the existing build already addresses `java.lang`, but am I ensuring coverage with internal JDK reflection correctly? There are likely issues due to JDK25 changes as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring security manager setup**\\n\\nI'm considering using the system property `-Djava.security.manager=allow`. It seems that older JDKs might require this setting to permit the use of `setSecurityManager`. It’s interesting how small adjustments like this can impact functionality. I want to ensure that I'm taking the right approach for compatibility and security, especially since configurations can vary across different JDK versions. Making the right choice here is crucial for smooth functioning in the existing environment.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating source inspection**\\n\\nI want to avoid modifying the build directory, so I need to check the source of OGNL 3.3.5 for any system properties. It’s important to read the relevant source snippets carefully to understand what I'm dealing with. I’ll make sure to take my time here, as I don't want to accidentally mess anything up while inspecting the source. Getting the details right is essential!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NfEaoVROX0GzMe9DdIt0kxi1|fc_007c4effd312dc10016a4285a597b88190aa92acf5e6732645", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; curl -sSfL -o ognl-3.3.5-sources.jar https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/ognl/ognl/3.3.5/ognl-3.3.5-sources.jar; jar xf ognl-3.3.5-sources.jar; python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=P